# Fluff Date: 2026-02-26 19:50:04
<overview>
<p>The Hellcat is a sixty-ton medium aerospace fighter introduced in 2671 by Mitchell Vehicles. Designed during a period of declining military expenditures following the Reunification War, the fighter was Mitchell's first foray into aerospace manufacturing after decades of producing ground combat vehicles. Though the Star League Defense Force found the design uninspiring due to its lack of advanced technology, the Hellcat earned a reputation among mercenary commands, private security firms, and militia forces who prized its rugged construction and minimal maintenance requirements. Licensed production by Lycomb-Davion IntroTech and Lockheed/CBM Corporation eventually spread the fighter across the Inner Sphere, and in the modern era, United Outworlders Corporation on Ramora produces an upgraded variant in partnership with Clan Snow Raven.</p>
</overview>

<capabilities>
<p>The Hellcat's designers approached aerospace engineering with the philosophy that sufficient thrust could make anything fly, resulting in a craft that prioritizes simplicity and survivability over sophistication. A GM 240 fusion engine provides adequate thrust, while a Lycomb 6 airframe gives the fighter a sturdy internal structure capable of absorbing considerable punishment. SlabPanzer 5 standard armor provides solid protection for the fighter's weight class, and the entire design emphasizes ease of field maintenance.</p><p>Armed exclusively with energy weapons, the Hellcat carries three Diverse Optics/A large lasers complemented by five Starflash medium lasers, giving it formidable strafing capability without any ammunition dependency. Twenty single heat sinks manage the thermal load from this all-laser armament. The fighter's five-ton fuel capacity represents its primary operational limitation, restricting extended patrol and pursuit missions. Telecron L50 communications and Telecron M75 targeting systems round out a straightforward but effective avionics package. The design excels in space operations where its energy-only loadout and rugged construction prove most advantageous.</p>
</capabilities>

<deployment>
<p>The HCT-313 represents a comprehensive modernization of the Hellcat design, developed jointly by Clan Snow Raven advisors and the United Outworlders Corporation on Ramora beginning in 3073. All heat sinks are upgraded to double-strength models, and the armor is replaced with heavy ferro-aluminum for significantly improved protection at equivalent weight. Lushann Industrials Limited high-quality lasers replace the original energy weapons, with all large lasers upgraded to extended-range models and the medium lasers to extended-range variants. This variant is deployed by both the Outworlds Alliance military and Clan Snow Raven second-line Clusters.</p>
</deployment>

<history>
<p>Mitchell Vehicles was a well-established combat vehicle and BattleMech manufacturer by the mid-twenty-seventh century, but the prolonged peace following the Reunification War drove the company to diversify into aerospace production. The first Hellcat prototype lifted off from Graham IV in 2671. Despite aggressive lobbying, the SLDF showed little interest in the untested design, viewing it as too unsophisticated for frontline service. Initial sales went entirely to the private sector, where shipping concerns and frontier security forces seeking affordable, low-maintenance fighters proved eager customers.</p><p>As privately owned Hellcats compiled an impressive combat record against pirates and raiders, SLDF interest grew. The fighter's ruggedness made it an excellent fit for garrison and second-line formations, and production expanded beyond Graham IV. Lycomb-Davion IntroTech established lines on New Avalon and Demeter in the Federated Suns, while Lockheed/CBM Corporation began manufacturing the fighter on Tharkad in the Lyran Commonwealth. A Mitchell Vehicles facility on Sirius V and another on Mars also contributed to the production base during the Star League era. Mitchell's own development of the related Hellcat II in 2710 did not diminish demand for the original design, as the two fighters filled different tactical roles and weight classes.</p><p>The destruction of Mitchell Vehicles' Graham IV plant in 2775 during the Amaris Civil War ended production of the original manufacturer's line, along with all Hellcat II production. The Sirius V facility continued producing Hellcats into the early Third Succession War before technological degradation forced its closure. The Demeter plant was destroyed by the Capellan Confederation during the First Succession War. However, the surviving Lycomb-Davion and Lockheed/CBM lines on New Avalon and Tharkad kept the Hellcat in continuous production through the Succession Wars, a feat few Star League-era fighters can claim. The Blakist sieges of both Tharkad and New Avalon during the Jihad finally ended these centuries-old production lines, with the Tharkad facility eventually rebuilt to produce the Morgenstern OmniFighter instead.</p><p>The Hellcat's story took an unexpected turn in the thirty-first century when the Outworlds Alliance, with Clan Snow Raven technical assistance, developed the HCT-313 upgrade at the United Outworlders Corporation plant on Ramora. Alliance pilots scored a notable victory over unidentified raiders at Ramora in 3074, and the Snow Ravens subsequently adopted the design for limited deployment in their second-line Clusters. This facility remains the only active Hellcat production line in the modern era.</p>
</history>

